text: Ekaterina Igorevna Valkova (, born 17 May 1991) is a Russian judoka who competes in the 63 kg division. In 2016, she won a bronze medal at the European championships, but was eliminated in the first round at the Rio Olympics. ==References== Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:People from Labinsk Category:Russian female judoka Category:Olympic judoka of Russia Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics
